## Typography-First Visual Design

No emoji in messages. Use clean typography and text labels:

| Need | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Severity | Bold text labels | `*Critical*`, `*High*`, `*Medium*`, `Low` |
| Score bars | Unicode block chars | `‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñà‚ñë‚ñë 80%` |
| Trends | Text deltas | `+3%`, `-2%`, `flat` |
| List items | Bullet points | `‚Ä¢ Item one` |
| Status | Plain text | `Active`, `At Risk`, `Stale (14 days)` |
| Emphasis | Bold/italic mrkdwn | `*Deal Name*`, `_context note_` |

## Slack Block Kit Limits (CRITICAL)

**Always respect these limits to avoid `invalid_blocks` errors:**

| Element | Limit |
|---------|-------|
| Header text | 150 characters |
| Section text | 3000 characters |
| Button text | 75 characters |
| Button value | 2000 characters |
| Context element text | 500 characters |
| Blocks per message | 50 blocks |
| Actions per block | 25 elements |
| Fields per section | 10 fields |

## Design Rules

1. **Max 3 buttons** per actions block (more creates decision fatigue)
2. **One primary button** per message (clear CTA hierarchy)
3. **Fields for pairs** - use section fields for label:value pairs
4. **Headers for alerts** - skip headers for routine updates
5. **Context for metadata** - timestamps, attributions at bottom
6. **Dividers sparingly** - only when switching topics
7. **URL buttons omit value** - don't include `value` when `url` is present

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

- **Too many blocks** - Keep under 10 blocks total
- **Wall of text** - Break into scannable chunks
- **No clear action** - Always include at least one button
- **Missing context** - Include who/when/why metadata
- **Emoji in messages** - Use text labels and bold instead
- **Button text too long** - Max 24 characters recommended
- **Value + URL on same button** - Slack may reject this
- **Exceeding character limits** - Truncate long text before building blocks
- **Missing deep links** - Every notification referencing a deal/contact/meeting must include a link footer

